itemListElement.name: Get Face-to-Face with Glaciers of Mt. Rainier

name: Get Face-to-Face with Glaciers of Mt. Rainier
description:
Most tours to Mt. Rainier focus on one location: Paradise. But Paradise, despite its name, is not the epitome of the Rainier experience. Bus loads of tourists take brief hikes on paved surfaces and crowd the trails. No solitude.

This adventure starts at Sunrise, a less-visited area, and brings you to the brink of Glacier Basin, where the largest glacier in the U.S. outside Alaska is front-and-center. 

On a summer weekday, you might have the trail and the views mostly to to yourselves (along with marmots, pikas, and goats).

Following this 6 to 9 mile hike (according to your preferences) we can reflect on the majesty of Rainier at a tavern for dinner or drinks or other refreshments.

name: Noi Thai Cuisine - Downtown Seattle
description:
Noi Thai Cuisine continues the traditional of Bai Tong Restaurants in Seattle, Washington which originally began as a favorite stopover for Thai Airways Crew at SeaTac Airport over two decades ago. 

At Noi Thai Cuisine Downtown Seattle, we pride ourselves on making high-quality food and giving our guests a real authentic Thai taste. We strive to bring our guests the best in Thai cuisine as our food is authentically prepared and beautifully presented. 

Here you will find your familiar favorites but even more dishes you may not be familiar with yet. Each dish on our menu is prepared to order using the freshest and highest quality ingredients. Most of our dishes are created and modified by one of the best chefs in Thailand.

 All of our dishes are prepared by our Executive Chef and his Thai culinary team with care to ensure our guests enjoy the best dining experience, so you can trust that every little detail has been taken care of.

name: Lake Union Boat Tour - 1hr
description:
1 Hour Private Tour on Lake Union - 14 person capacity

Spend an hour cruising by Gas Works Park, past the floating homes and enjoy a relaxing cruise around Lake Union.

Great for a date night or a friends evening out on the water, Mocha is a 26ft open boat with unobstructed views of downtown and the Space Needle. Bring your own light snacks and drinks for this engaging experience on the water.

review.name: Wonderful 1-Hour Scenic Tour of Lake Union
review.reviewBody: My coworkers and I were in town for a conference and wanted to see the lake.  I found Lake Union Charters & Adventures online and it was very easy to make a reservation for the 1-hour Lake Union scenic tour.  Moti was a wonderful captain and tour guide.  We were able to see the houseboat from Sleepless in Seattle, the Gasworks Park from 10 Things I Hate About You, several houseboat communities and stunning views.  We also had a wonderful view of the Space Needle. I would highly recommend using Lake Union Charters & Adventures - it was very easy and the service was wonderful!

itemListElement.name: Bon Vivant Woodinville Wine Tasting Tour

name: Bon Vivant Woodinville Wine Tasting Tour
description:
Bon Vivants popular wine tasting tours are led by professionally wine educated tour guides. Here's what you can expect:
 >Your group's wine preferences will influence tour stop choices for the day
 >From your Seattle Hotel, you'll enjoy a comfortable 30 minute drive from Seattle to Woodinville, crossing beautiful Lake Washington, to Wine Country
 >Visiting a flagship winery starts the touring day off big
 >A boutique winery will be next, where you can purchase lunch to enjoy while tasting
 >The afternoon will find you visiting 2 boutique wineries and tasting rooms, we call them hidden gems. (There are 140+ to choose from!) En route, your guide will talk about the next winery on your custom tour, the winemaker, their history, etc.
 >You will be returned to your point of departure around 4:30
 >All day long, you will be treated to your tour guide's insights and Washington Wine Country knowledge.
 >And best of all, you will go home with happy memories!

review.name: Perfect sister trip
review.reviewBody: Rudy was exceptionally knowledgeable about the wines and the region. He was a super tour guide. And each winery was a different, interesting experience.

review.name: Highly recommend this tour
review.reviewBody: Wonderful tour. We were picked up by Michael who was a really nice, friendly person. The vehicle was clean and Michael was right on time. He had a lot of knowledge of the area, the local wines, and the various wineries.  He took us to some great locations. The lunch location was great. The food was wonderful. I highly recommend this tour if you want to get acquainted with some great Washington wines.

review.name: Best Wine Tasting Experience
review.reviewBody: Rudy was an outstanding driver and guide for our wine tour! He was very knowledgeable having former experience in the wine industry. He knew everybody at all of our stops and we felt like we were VIPs the entire day. The wine tasting experiences were all very good and at 1 stop we even got a tour of the winery by the owner himself who was very passionate about his craft. I highly recommend this tour for anyone wanting to learn and enjoy a great wine tasting experience! Thank you Rudy and Su for making our anniversary trip extra special for us! Cheers!

review.name: Excellent Tour To Woodinville Wine Country
review.reviewBody:
Michael was a wonderful guide on our first foray into Washington wine country. My husband and I felt very well taken care of and the wine tastings were excellent. 
Highly recommend and have already referred some friends to them when they are in town. Don't delay book right away!

review.name: Cork Dork for the WIN!
review.reviewBody: This was our second tour with Bon Vivant and it did not disappoint!  We were able to customize the stops based on what we knew we liked and places we'd already been to.  We loved the composition of the tour:  introduction to the winery, history of the winemakers, some special features, then time to chat amongst ourselves as we taste.  Peter was our tour guide and he's pretty darn knowledgable, and as a self-professed Cork Dork, he was able to answer literally any question we threw at him.  Would definitely take this tour again, even more fun with friends!

review.name: Wine tour
review.reviewBody: Rudy was wonderful - we bonded over Wisconsin football and Jonathan Taylor - wine was lovely!!! Would definitely recommend - prefer the small boutiques for sure!

review.name: Meh
review.reviewBody: I don't feel the tour was "designed around the tasting preferences of that days tour guests", as described on the web site.  We were never asked about our wine preferences.  With that said, on the 3rd stop, Peter did take us to a different winery then the others in the group after our disappointment was apparent.  I was surprised that most wineries had a preset tasting menu - a combination of whites and reds - regardless if you didn't drink one of them.  Peter's knowledge of the science of wine and talking with one of the owners was the highlight of the trip.

review.name: Woodinville a must visit!
review.reviewBody: I had a relative visiting from out of town and booked this tour so that I could do my first Woodinville wine tasting! Peter, our tour guide, was wonderful company and chose a nice selection of wineries for us to visit. I highly recommend this tour and will be doing it again soon with friends.

review.name: Fun day in Woodinville
review.reviewBody:
Peter picked us up at our hotel promptly as scheduled. What a wealth of knowledge! He talked to us about the area in general and the specific wines that we tasted. He explained things in a very understandable way. It was a leisurely way to spend a day in Seattle.
The pours in the wineries/tasting rooms were generous. After the first tasting, we shared one and that was enough for us.
I would highly recommend this tour.

review.name: Great time with Rudy and new friends
review.reviewBody: Fabulous time tasting all the wonderful wines! The highlight was definitely our tour guide Rudy! He is fantastic and made our day!!

mainEntity.name: How many wines will we taste at each stop on the Bon Vivant Woodinville Wine Tasting Tour?

acceptedAnswer.text: Typically, you will taste 4-7 wines at each tasting stop. As we will visit 4-6 wineries, these 1oz tastings can add up to several glasses of wine. To keep your taste buds fresh, we provide bottled water between each stop.

mainEntity.name: Are tasting fees included on the Bon Vivant Woodinville Wine Tasting Tour?

acceptedAnswer.text: Tasting fees are not included. Most wineries charge $10 to $15. Some wineries offer special reserve wine tastings for an additional fee. Some wineries waive their fees for our guests and the tasting fee is often waived with the purchase of a bottle.

mainEntity.name: Where do we have lunch on the Bon Vivant Woodinville Wine Tasting Tour?

acceptedAnswer.text: We will make reservations at a leading locally owned, winery district restaurant or wine bar, where you may select and purchase your own meal.

mainEntity.name: Which types of wine will we encounter on the Bon Vivant Woodinville Wine Tasting Tour?

acceptedAnswer.text: Although Washington first gained a reputation with white wines like Riesling in the 1960s, current Washington wine production is about 57% red and 43% white wine. Just let your guide know your preferences and we will tailor your trip accordingly.

itemListElement.name: Cheese, Tequila and a Mexican Feast

name: Cheese, Tequila and a Mexican Feast
description:
Brian and Holly are Gilbert's Cheese Experience. We host cheese-pairing pop-ups that combine locally procured food and beverages with insider access to craft producers. 

This is an exciting new type of event: a "cheesemonger's dinner," featuring a chef-created tasting menu with cheese in every course! We're teaming up with the Atrium Kitchen at Pike Place Market to bring you an international evening of food and spirits from the heart of Seattle's food culture. Chef Traci is preparing a Mexican feast, and Casa Noble tequila will be there supplying beverages.
